					<h3 class="heading pb-4 underline-heading">Engineering Economics & Accounting</h3>

					<h5 class="course-heading">Course Objectives:</h5>

					<p>To help the students to acquire conceptual knowledge of Economic Laws, Financial Accounting and 
application of principles and practices of Financial Management in the decision-making process to justify 
or reject long term investment proposals.
</p>

					<h6 class="course-heading">Module I</h6>
					<p>Economics- Nature and scope, The theory of demand, demand function, law of demand and its exceptions, 
Elasticity of demand, Law of supply and elasticity of supply. Determination of equilibrium price under 
perfect competition (Simple Numerical problems to be solved).
</p>


					<h6 class="course-heading">Module II</h6>
					<p>Cost Concepts, Elements of cost, Segregation of costs into Fixed and variable costs. Break-even AnalysisLinear Approach. (Simple Numerical problems to be solved). Depreciation Policy, Depreciation of capital 
assets, Causes of depreciation, Straight line method and declining balance method</p>

					<h6 class="course-heading">Module III</h6>
					<p>Accounting process and principles, Elements of book keeping, Journal, , Ledger, cash book, Bank reconciliation 
statement, trial balance, profit and loss accounts, final accounts of proprietary and partnership concern and 
balance sheet. Cash Flow Analysis.</p>


					<h6 class="course-heading">Module IV</h6>
					<p>Financial Management – Meaning, scope and role, Time value of money. Long Term Investment DecisionPayback period method, Present worth method, Future worth method, Annual worth method, Internal rate 
of return method. Ratio Analysis, Types of ratios. Budgeting – budgets, purpose, budgetary control, 
preparation of budgets master budget, fixed and flexible budgeting.</p>


					<h6 class="course-heading">Course Outcomes:</h6>
					<p> Be able to understand the Microeconomic laws.
					    Be able to evaluate the corporate governance structure of a firm and long term investment decisions.
                        Memorize how to calculate Break Even Point and Depreciation by applying various methods.
                        Be able to maintain the financial statements of a business entity</p>
						
